{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6151e8634508da32e9e96e70", "type": "numerical", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb98"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "96", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "The figure shows a block of mass m resting on a horizontal smooth floor at a distance <math><mi>l</mi></math> from a rigid wall. Block is pushed toward the right by a distance <math><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> and released from rest. When block passes from its mean position, another block of mass <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> is gently placed on it which sticks to it due to friction. The value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> so that the combined block just touches the left wall is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>\u03b7</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi></math>. Find the value of <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03b7</mi></math>.<br />\r<br />\r<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/nta_abhyas/jee_main/images/4e3c6699-d22f-409c-822c-3259e1a329a4-image17.jpeg\" style=\"max-width:100%; object-fit:contain\" style=\"height: 116px; width: 250px;\" />", "image": null}, "options": [], "correctValue": "5", "solution": {"text": "When block P is released from rest from a distance <math><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> toward right from mean position, this will be the amplitude of oscillation so velocity of block when passing from its mean position is given as<br /><math><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>\u03c9</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math><br />If mass m<sub>1</sub> is added to it and just after if velocity of combined block becomes v<sub>1</sub>, from momentum conservation, we have<br />mv = (m + m<sub>1</sub>)v<sub>1</sub><br /><math><mo>\u2234</mo><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>\u22c5</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math><br />If this is the velocity of combined block at mean position, it is given as<br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03c9</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math> where <math><msub><mrow><mi>\u03c9</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math><br />where A<sub>1</sub> and <math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03c9</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math> are the new amplitude and angular frequency of SHM of the block.<br />It is given that combined block just reaches the left wall.<br />Thus, the new amplitude of oscillation must be <math><mi>l</mi></math> . So, we have,<br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>\u22c5</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mi>l</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math><br />On solving, we get<br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>m</mi></math><br /><math><mo>\u2234</mo><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["616023f6105ab3ae165341bb", "61964c8546e3d33b1892d09e", "61c089968734366dae3f36bc", "61bb8217aebeece6abdbe72b", "616023f783ceaeb51fe46126", "616023f4946fab7b921bf28d", "61964c86b98428bab9bd89d6", "616023f51f5c75c27ba35382", "616023f36324da677f8a7444", "61e7bd75347c64f272d9d8bb", "62962124ca45d71899e3dfe9", "629f390dd4f42c0deef34eab", "629109ef78779344f598426c", "629f3a921cf4dc490b09a322", "64eb06c13118f713ecfef085", "66d5853ca75f05ee8564f57b", "67921d681d5b5072da5e9acb", "67fdff4e378e1624ea7b69f4", "6809202b3a10446a207fdee4"], "cpyqbExams": ["615f0e999476412f48314daf", "616059af0283de43c87e3e23"]}}